{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> πλάξ</b>, πλᾰκός, ἡ, <br /> <b>anything flat and broad</b>, especially <b>flat land, plain</b>, πᾶσαν ἠπείρου πλάκα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Persae” 718 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; Φλεγραίαν π. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Eu.” 295 \">Refs</a>]; νυχίαν π., of Psyttaleia (perhaps μυχίαν), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] “Pers.” 953 (Lyric poetry); πλακὸς ὑλίας “Berl.Sitzb.” 1927.7 (_Locrian dialect_, 5th c.BC)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; νεκύων πλάκα [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 1564 (Lyric poetry); νεκρῶν πλάκες [prev. work] 1577 (Lyric poetry)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; also of sea and sky, πόντου πλάξ the ocean-<b>plain</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 1.24; ἄλοκα Νηρεΐας πλακὸς τέμνοντες 6th c.BC: Arion Lyricus 1.15 \">Refs 6th c.BC+</a>]; ποντία, πελαγία π., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Fragmenta” 578.4, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Ranae” 1438; κατ᾽ Αἰγαίην πόντου πλάκα “BMus.Inscription” 1012 (Chalcedon, 1st c.BC-1st c.AD)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; αἰθερία πλάξ [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Electra” 1349 (_anapaest meter_)\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>flat top of a hill, table-land</b>, Σουνίου, Οἴτης π., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Ajax” 1220, “Ph.” 1430; Παρνασοῦ πλάκες 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Ion” 1267 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἀπ᾽ ἄκρας πυργώδους πλακός from the <b>flat top</b> of the towering hill, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 273; τὰς π. τοῦ ὄρους 2nd c.AD(?): Antoninus Liberalis Mythographus 4.1. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>flat stone, tablet</b>, ἐργώνας τᾶν πλακῶν τᾶς τομᾶς εἰς τὸν ὀχετόν [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\